name: Isadora Loyola
bio:
Born in Rio de Janeiro, Brasil 🇧🇷. Now living in NYC 🗽,and dancing with American Ballet Theater. 🩰 
♑️🕉☯️

social_posts.post_text: Ending the year with a special bday 🎊 feeling so loved from all the messages and posts, I wish I could personally celebrate it with every single one of you. But just know that your energy was definitely there with me! Love you all 🤍🕊️🎊🙏🏽

“Night Pieces” by Duncan Lyle @duncanlyledance is out now!!! 💙 
Link in bio! 

#newworks #choreographer #ballet #freeart

#dld2023digitalseason has officially begun! Link in bio, to watch this beautiful piece for free on his YouTube channel! 
Here is a little tease during my Cinderella moment with @mikey_delanuez ✨

“Whaaaat?” Hahaha 😝 
Just holding on to this passé as long as I can. 😅

Thank you @seanstewartnyc for a great class that kept me on my leg 💃🏻 and to @cydoherty for capturing this moment 🫶🏽 

#pirouettes #bestfeelingever #mondayfunday

First tour of 2023 done ✔️ it was a lovely week performing with my friends and family (hubby). Congratulations to everyone that was part of this beautiful production of R&J! See you at the Met! ❤️‍🔥

#abt #r&j #washingtonDC #kennedycenter #tourlife #artist #performance

Had the pleasure to be photographed by @markmannphoto in the summer of 2021, and now it’s in a beautiful book by @rizzolibooks 🤩

#Movementatthestillpoint or #MATSPbook

All profits from the book will be shared equally with all dancers in the book.

That’s wrap for now for “Like Water for Chocolate” choreographed by @wheeldony ❤️‍🔥🌹 Looking forward to revisiting this beautiful production again at the @metopera this summer🌞 

1. Group pic

Thank you @cassandratrenary for the 🎥
Chi-town you were real. Short and kinda sweet🍬💘🔫🌃

Short but very sweet trip to my home country. Family time has always been so precious to me, since I left home so young. Very grateful to had spent Mother’s Day with my mum @loyolanadja 💗🕊️ 20 years later, made it extra special. 🥰 te amo mãe 💖🥲
